                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Farhang-i Muḥammad Shāhī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">فرهنگ محمد شاهی</title>
                     <note>F1a: Printed bookplate of Sani' al-Daula Muhammad Hasan Khan dated 1298. Later entitled I'timad al-Saltana he was one of Nasir al-Din Shah's ministers. On the bookplate the signature of Ellis. Front flyleaf, verso: account in siyaq. Under end of text: impression of rectangular seal of 'Abd al-Rahim. After text several folios with ruled margins, some coloured. These and the flyleaves have bits of poetry etc written on them. A Persian dictionary, written at the suggestion of Prince Bahman Mirza for presentation to his brother, the future Muhammad Shah. Ruled and gilded margins. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Al-hamdu lillah alladhi khalaqa al-wara</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, iii, pp. 49-50.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, Suppt p. 119.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Storey list no other MS; a later version, the Burhan-i Jami' is more common.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
